@startuml CreazioneMailService
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor White
skinparam participant {
    BackgroundColor LightBlue
    BorderColor DarkBlue
}
skinparam actor {
    BackgroundColor LightGreen
    BorderColor DarkGreen
}
skinparam database {
    BackgroundColor LightYellow
    BorderColor Orange
}

title Creazione Servizio Mail

actor Utente
participant "PageProcedureLavorazioni" as Page
participant "DialogAddBackgroundTask" as Dialog
participant "MailImportHandlerRegistry" as Registry
participant "ServiceProcedureLavorazioni" as Service
participant "ProductionJobScheduler" as Scheduler
participant "Hangfire" as HF
database "TaskDaEseguire" as DB

Utente -> Page: 1. Modifica Procedura esistente\n(Edit mode)
activate Page
Page -> Dialog: 2. Apre dialog per fase specifica\ncon contesto procedura
activate Dialog

Dialog -> Registry: 3. Carica service codes disponibili\nvia HandlerRegistry.Codes
activate Registry
Registry -> Dialog: 4. Lista service codes:\n["HERA16.EWS", "EQ4.VR", "EQ4.GE"]
deactivate Registry

Utente -> Dialog: 5. Seleziona "HERA16.EWS"\ndal dropdown Mail Service
Dialog -> Dialog: 6. Disabilita automaticamente\ncampi query/connection
Dialog -> Dialog: 7. Popola MailServiceCode\nnel TaskDaEseguireDto
Dialog -> Page: 8. Restituisce TaskDaEseguireDto\ncon MailServiceCode valorizzato
deactivate Dialog

Page -> Service: 9. UpdateProceduraLavorazione\nAndFasiDataReadingAsync()
activate Service
Service -> DB: 10. UPDATE TaskDaEseguire\ncon MailServiceCode
Service -> Page: 11. Success response
deactivate Service

Page -> Scheduler: 12. SyncAllAsync()\nper schedulazione mail
activate Scheduler
Scheduler -> DB: 13. Carica task mail\n(MailServiceCode != null)
Scheduler -> Scheduler: 14. BuildHangfireKey()\nmail:{id}-{proc}:{service}
Scheduler -> HF: 15. AddOrUpdate(mailKey, idTask, cron)
activate HF
HF -> HF: 16. Schedula recurring job mail\ncon ProductionJobRunner.RunAsync
deactivate HF
deactivate Scheduler
deactivate Page

note right of HF: Job mail schedulato\nper importazione automatica

@enduml